[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m `referral_breadth` is a count (number of distinct specialists referred to). Applying linear regression and O/E ratios to count data is conceptually awkward (expected values can be fractional, O/E ratios for small counts are unstable). For the synthetic data with values ranging 2-30, this works fine in practice. A brief comment noting that count metrics might benefit from Poisson regression in production would be helpful but is not required.
